# Update System Documentation

When you make **meaningful changes** to ZSMS, update `docs/SYSTEM_DOCUMENTATION.md` in the **same session** before finishing. Bump the **Last updated** date (YYYY-MM-DD) at the top of that file.

## When to update (required)

| Change type | Update these sections |
| ----------- | --------------------- |
| New/removed API routes or conventions | API conventions, Core domains, Related docs; run `npm run docs:api-routes` |
| Prisma schema / tenancy model | Data model overview, Core domains |
| Auth, proxy.js, CSRF, CSP, RLS | Security model, System architecture |
| New integration or env var | Integrations, Environment variables; also `docs/ENVIRONMENT.md` if new var |
| Deployment, migrations, CI | Deployment and migrations |
| New dashboard role or portal | User roles and portals |
| Mobile API or zsms-mobile scope | Mobile app section |
| Major new module (ECZ, timetable, billing, etc.) | Core domains table, Executive summary if user-facing |
| Tech stack version bumps (Next, Prisma, Expo) | Technology stack table, header version note |

## When to skip

- Typo fixes, copy changes, or styling-only edits
- Test-only changes with no behavior/API/schema impact
- Refactors that do not change architecture or external contracts

## How to update

1. Read the current `docs/SYSTEM_DOCUMENTATION.md`.
2. Edit only sections affected by your change; keep pointers to deeper docs (do not duplicate DEVELOPER_GUIDE content).
3. Verify paths and names against the actual codebase.
4. Set **Last updated** to today's date.

If unsure whether a change is "meaningful," update the doc — prefer accuracy over omission.
